    <string name="elemental_amount_unit_unit_title">Measurement Unit</string>
    <string name="elemental_amount_unit_unit_body">In Genshin Impact elements system, there is no official elemental measurement unit for determining amount of element, like <b><i>mol</i></b> in chemistry in real life.\nSo, we consider using <b><i>Element Unit (EU)</i></b> as the measurement unit by dividing weak elemental attachment into 100 equal pieces, and thus weak elemental attachment is <b><i>100EU</i></b>.</string>
    <string name="elemental_amount_unit_amount_title">Elemental Amount Attached</string>
    <string name="elemental_amount_unit_amount_body">There are 3 types of element attached amount to target available, <b><i>Weak</i></b>, <b><i>Strong</i></b> and <b><i>Super</i></b>, in ratio <b><i>1:2:4</i></b>.</string>
